            {
              "__typename": "IssueComment",
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6eorOd",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T14:43:21Z",
              "body": "### PR summary [982270fde2](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/21955/commits/982270fde2902796d431bf32c99391dd31c4c339)\n\n#### Import changes for modified files\n\nNo significant changes to the import graph\n\n\n<details><summary>Import changes for all files</summary>\n\n|Files|Import difference|\n|-|-|\n| `Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.Tight` (new file)|1379|\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n<details><summary>\n\n#### Declarations diff\n\n</summary>\n\n`+ IsTightMeasureSet`\n`+ IsTightMeasureSet_iff_exists_isCompact_measure_compl_le`\n`+ inter`\n`+ isTightMeasureSet_singleton_of_innerRegular`\n`+ isTightMeasureSet_singleton_of_innerRegularWRT`\n`+ of_compactSpace`\n`+ subset`\n`+ union`\n<details>\n  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>\n\n\n```bash\n## summary with just the declaration names:\n./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>\n\n## more verbose report:\n./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>\n```\n</details>\n\nThe doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n<details><summary>No changes to technical debt.</summary>\n\nYou can run this locally as\n```\n./scripts/technical-debt-metrics.sh pr_summary\n```\n* The `relative` value is the weighted *sum* of the differences with weight given by the *inverse* of the current value of the statistic.\n* The `absolute` value is the `relative` value divided by the total sum of the inverses of the current values (i.e. the weighted *average* of the differences).\n</details>\n",
              "author": {
                "login": "github-actions"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "PullRequestCommit",
              "commit": {
                "oid": "8611ab114e028e73318d5825bdce9d72e9c31db5"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "UnlabeledEvent",
              "id": "UNLE_lADOFcwZ1c6qPT5qzwAAAAPNCmtW",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T18:35:13Z",
              "label": {
                "id": "MDU6TGFiZWwzMjcxMjQ0NzU5",
                "name": "WIP"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "AssignedEvent",
              "id": "AE_lADOFcwZ1c6qPT5qzwAAAAPNCntl",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T18:37:08Z",
              "assignee": {
                "id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY2ODQ3MjYy",
                "login": "EtienneC30"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "IssueComment",
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6epEKY",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T18:43:16Z",
              "body": "How does this relate to #19780, which proved that probability measures on Polish spaces are tight, but without using the word tight?",
              "author": {
                "login": "sgouezel"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "IssueComment",
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6epHLi",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T19:17:50Z",
              "body": "Indeed the other PR proved this:\r\n```lean\r\ntheorem PolishSpace.innerRegular_isCompact_isClosed_measurableSet [TopologicalSpace α]\r\n    [PolishSpace α] [BorelSpace α] (P : Measure α) [IsFiniteMeasure P] :\r\n    P.InnerRegularWRT (fun s ↦ IsCompact s ∧ IsClosed s) MeasurableSet\r\n```\r\nThe last result of this PR proves\r\n```lean\r\ninstance [T2Space α] [OpensMeasurableSpace α] [IsFiniteMeasure μ] [μ.InnerRegular] : IsTight μ\r\n```\r\nAnd I just remembered that the `T2Space` argument is only there to ensure that compact sets are closed. The better statement should be\r\n```lean\r\ntheorem isTight_of_innerRegularWRT [OpensMeasurableSpace α] [IsFiniteMeasure μ]\r\n    (h : μ.InnerRegularWRT (fun s ↦ IsCompact s ∧ IsClosed s) MeasurableSet) :\r\n    IsTight μ\r\n```",
              "author": {
                "login": "RemyDegenne"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "LabeledEvent",
              "id": "LE_lADOFcwZ1c6qPT5qzwAAAAPNDASJ",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T19:24:09Z",
              "label": {
                "id": "LA_kwDOFcwZ1c7P265b",
                "name": "awaiting-author"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "IssueComment",
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6epJfw",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T19:45:05Z",
              "body": "I guess a question is whether we need a new definition for a tight measure (tight sets of measures we definitely want). It's not clear to me if there are settings where the definition IsTight is different from some form of InnerRegular and the tight measure property is interesting.",
              "author": {
                "login": "RemyDegenne"
              }
            },
            {
              "__typename": "IssueComment",
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6epNo0",
              "createdAt": "2025-02-16T20:31:42Z",
              "body": "If I'm not mistaken, tightness always implies `innerRegularWRT IsCompact IsClosed`, and the converse is true for ~~σ-finite~~ finite measures. I don't think it will be possible to get a version for any measure though, but I think this is not really needed. From my limited experience with tightness what we want is either a tight set of measures for results about the topology over measures or a tight indexed family for some convergence results. I don't think tightness of a single measure is really worth adding. Maybe we can add in the doc that this case is most of the time covered by `innerRegularWRT`.",
              "author": {
                "login": "EtienneC30"
              }
            },
            {
